i%20continues%20to%20be%20loved%20across%20India%20and%20the%20world%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Instagram%3A%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ffoodgramkolkata%2Fp%2FCAXn2RIHZhW%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Food%20Gram%20Kolkata%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFans%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Erosogolla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20attention!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20how%20the%20sweet%20came%20to%20be%20is%20a%20fine%20example%20of%20what%20can%20transpire%20with%20a%20little%20innovation.%20The%20%3Cem%3Erosogolla%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20result%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331406%2Fwrestler-parmanand-jain-started-mahaveer-rabri-bhandar-became-iconic-eatery-of-jaipur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20afternoon%20experiment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201868%20by%20a%20man%20named%20Nobin%20Chandra%20Das.%20Rolling%20balls%20of%20curdled%20milk%20and%20then%20boiling%20them%20in%20sugar%20syrup%20resulted%20in%20the%20beloved%20sweet%20that%20Kolkata%20and%20the%20globe%20adore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20article%20in%20%3Cem%3EForbes%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20was%20a%20fan%20of%20the%20place%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Erosogollas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20story%20is%20often%20retold%20of%20a%20time%20Tagore%20was%20served%20a%20pot%20of%20%3Cem%3Erosogollas%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20one%20of%20his%20acquaintances.%20Tagore%20nibbled%20at%20one%20and%20then%20asked%20if%20it%20was%20Das%20who%20had%20prepared%20these.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t.%20Tagore%20then%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20must%20feed%20me%20%3Cem%3Erosogollas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20make%20sure%20it%E2%80%99s%20from%20Nobin%E2%80%99s.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Balaram%20Mullick%20%26amp%3B%20Radharaman%20Mullick%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F9PyJRkvY2N4%3Fsi%3DCNb57CyOliMrajEH%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20guest%20list%20at%20this%20144-year-old%20sweet%20shop%20has%20always%20been%20coloured.%20From%20journalists%2C%20the%20likes%20of%20Barkha%20Dutt%20and%20Prannoy%20Roy%3B%20and%20celebrities%2C%20the%20likes%20of%20Ranbir%20Kapoor%2C%20to%20legendary%20figures%20such%20as%20Ashutosh%20Mukherjee%20(a%20prominent%20Bengali%20educator)%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20seems%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F208578%2Fvegan-chocolate-dairy-free-cookies-healthy-cake-options-millet-recipes-order-online-lifestyle-tan42%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelished%20the%20fares%3C%2Fa%3E%20served%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20founder%20Ganesh%20Chandra%20Mullick%20came%20to%20Kolkata%20from%20Konnagar%20in%201880.%20He%20worked%20for%20three%20years%20as%20a%20sweet%20%3Cem%3Ekarigar%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20North%20Kolkata%20shop%20before%20setting%20up%20Balaram%20Mullick%20%26amp%3B%20Radharaman%20Mullick%20in%201883%20in%20Bhowanipore%20(South%20Kolkata)%20on%20a%20450%20sq%20ft%20land.%20The%20eatery%20is%20now%20famous%20for%20its%20%3Cem%3Ekorapak%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20Bengali%20sweet%20made%20with%20cottage%20cheese)%20and%20%3Cem%3Enolen%20gur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20special%20jaggery%20found%20in%20Bengal).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Emergency%2C%20when%20milk%20was%20banned%2C%20the%20women%20of%20the%20family%20stepped%20up%20to%20create%20sweets%20out%20of%20cashews%20and%20pulses%20to%20keep%20the%20business%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Chittaranjan%20Mistanna%20Bhandar%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20draw%20here%20is%20the%20spongy%2C%20sweet%2C%20dribbling%20in%20sugar%20syrup%20%3Cem%3Erosogolla.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20iconic%20Chittaranjan%20Mistanna%20Bhandar%20is%20one%20of%20the%2071%20certified%20sweet%20shops%20in%20the%20city%20to%20sell%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F225831%2Fnortheast-india-food-gi-tag-chak-hao-rice-boka-saul-queen-pineapple-superfood-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20GI%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Cem%3Erosogollas%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20this%20115-year-old%20eatery%20are%20delightful%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20the%20sweet%20outlet%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ERosogolla%20Wala%20of%20Kolkata%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20their%20%3Cem%3Emadhuporko%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20sweet%20made%20from%20curd%2C%20ghee%20and%20honey)%20is%20equally%20amazing.%20And%20a%20fan%20of%20it%20is%20none%20other%20than%20Indian%20chef%20Saransh%20Goila.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxLiAgsgoMuM%3Fsi%3DZHrL2_-z6II9NI70%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Girish%20Chandra%20Dey%20And%20Nakur%20Chandra%20Nandy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20love%20Calcutta.%20The%20food%20is%20just%20brilliant.%20Every%20time%20I%20go%2C%20I%20must%20have%20sweets%20from%20Nakur%20(Girish%20Chandra%20Dey%20%26amp%3B%20Nakur%20Chandra%20Nandy)%2C%20especially%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejolbhora%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Emanohara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20celebrity%20chef%20Ranveer%20Brar%20shared%20in%20an%20article%20with%3Cem%3E%20Telegraph%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eatery%20is%20a%20renowned%20one%20in%20Kolkata%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F235277%2Findian-traditional-food-dessert-sweets-beautiful-art-festive-cuisin